Noises

empirical

It’s so quiet right now. I can hear the wind rushing past the closed window beside my bed, trying to get through it. Ticking of the clock and sound of insects. I can also hear the breathing of others in the neighbouring room indicating that they’re already asleep.

My eyes are also heavy which is, to be honest, unusual for me. It might be possible that I’m exhausted, as it was a long day with a lot of noises.

Noises that can make you tired.
